node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Our own Martin @breadwright is making Neapolitan-Style pizzas with our ‘00’ Pizza Flour and @BelGioiosoCheese, so fire up your grill, grab your ingredients, and join in on the fun!

Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text:
We're excited to announce that #KingArthurBaking Company has been recognized as #BFTW2021! This means we scored in the top 5% of one of the five impact areas assessed as part of the B Corp certification process. We're proud to be Best For The World™ and a part of the global #BCorp community.

One unique benefit offered to our employee-owners is that every year, we're allotted 40 hours of paid volunteer time. In 2020, there were over 6,000 collective hours spent volunteering across our company! Learn more about King Arthur's volunteer program and check out the full Best for the World 2021 list by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A blueberry pie with two slices removed and served on small plates. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Perfect blueberry pie filling … without an oven? The beauty of fresh blueberries is the juicy “pop” as you bite into them. This deliciously satisfying feature is usually lost in pie, as they take on a soft, squishy texture. Here’s the good news: you can have your pie and eat it too. Check out our blog at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for the secret to creating fresh blueberry pie, and share yours with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: Brownies that have been cut into diamond shapes, on a piece of brown parchment paper with a cup of coffee next to it. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: The secret to making seriously incredible brownies? Almond flour! In this naturally #GrainFree recipe, our Baking Sugar Alternative makes these ultra-moist and fudgy brownies a guilt-free treat. They’re perfectly Sweet, Not Sugary. Find this and our collection of other Sweet Not Sugary recipes at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your brownies with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: For maximum fluffy goodness, keep your Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls separated. They will NOT dry out! This recipe was designed to be moist and tender, and it's packed with tips to keep them that way. Bake a batch today: bakewith.us/ROTY2021

node.accessibility_caption: A photo of a large field of wheat at sunset with a combine working in the distance. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: With organic farmer, Bob Baker, by his side, @breadwright walked through Bob’s wheat fields in Alva, Oklahoma, learning about his work in organic farming. From meticulously controlling soil health to supplying habitats for ladybugs and other beneficial insects, growing organic wheat is a complex and challenging process. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to hear Bob’s story and see how his organic wheat eventually becomes our organic flour.

node.accessibility_caption: A photo of a large field of wheat at sunset with a combine working in the distance. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking
A photo of Bob in his wheat field. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking
A close up of the shafts of wheat  lowing in the breeze and a small bug flying through them. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking
A baker loading a pizza into a brick, wood-fired oven. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: If you’ve been dreaming of building a wood-fired oven in your community or even just in your backyard, this is the place to start. @breadwright is here to break down the pros and cons of wood-fired oven styles so you can figure out which design will work best for you. Check it out at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your oven journey with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A large quiche in the lower right hand corner of the photo with a baking sheet holding four mini tarts in the upper left hand corner. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Gardens overrun with zucchini is a given, but today we’re tackling the abundance of another summer star: tomatoes. 🍅 When all your plants fruit at once, your garden produces more tomatoes than your daily salad can handle. Enter: Fresh Tomato Tarts! Flaky, buttery pastry, slices of juicy tomato, and a rich cheesy filling make for to-die-for individual appetizer tarts or a full-size quiche. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your tomato bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A round pavlova topped with whipped cream, fresh raspberries and strawberries, and mint leaves.

node.text: Like a swimming pool of berries and clouds, a pavlova is nothing short of a summer dessert dream. In a crisp-on-the-outside, marshmallowy-on-the-inside meringue shell, freshly whipped cream and ripe fruit find themselves right at home. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for the recipe, and share your pavlova with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: Chocolate chip cookies, some on a cooling rack, some on a plate, and one broken into pieces on the table. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: If #NationalChocolateChipCookieDay snuck up on you, don’t worry! 🍪 Our #1 recipe is not only the perfect combination of chewy, crispy, crunchy, and bendy, but they’ll be in and out of the oven in just over half an hour. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share what you bake for National Chocolate Chip Cookie Day with #KingArthurBaking.

node.text: The dentist didn't prescribe this kind of flossing — the King did. 👑 These Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls are beautifully and cleanly sliced with floss in no time with our #recipeoftheyear at bakewith.us/ROTY2021

node.accessibility_caption: A decadent rocky road brownie perfect for any time. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: One scoop of rocky road is never enough. So how about a whole TRAY of rocky road brownie goodness? With a basic brownie mix (like our #GlutenFree Fudge Brownie Mix used here), you can replicate the nostalgic flavors and textures of rocky road ice cream. Marshmallows, pecans, chocolate, and caramel make for a brownie you won’t soon forget. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share how you serve up your batch (sundaes anyone?) with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A chocolate pound cake baked in a Bundt pan and topped with a chocolate glaze. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: When the 3:00 p.m. droopy eyes hit, snack time is in order. This chocolate rendition of a classic pound cake gets the mocha treatment with one of our favorite ingredients: espresso powder. If you want the coffee flavor to REALLY stand out, swap out the water for coffee in the cake and the topping. We’ll pop a recipe you can grab a glaze from (just substitute the water in it with coffee!) and the recipe for this divine pound cake at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Share your 3:00 snack faves with #KingArthurBaking
